The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

 Metro briefs

 The management-staff stand-off at the Citimart chain of stores took a turn for the worse on Thursday, after the Citu-affiliated workers union struck work at the Rashbehari branch and gheraoed the management at Lighthouse cinema.

 he employees are demanding permanent status and reinstatement of suspended staff. 

 ohn Mantosh, the owner of the Citimart chain, however, accused the union of strong-arm tactics. They beat up my manager, went on a wildcat strike in June and forced me to shift my central godown to Lucknow. They have violated every high court order, he said.

 Dahesin Fatema, 13, and her one-year-old brother were returned to their father Mohammad Rizwan on Thursday morning, almost 16 hours after they went missing. Dahesin, mentally deranged, and her brother had arrived in the city with their parents a few days ago from Muzzafarpur, said an officer of Ekbalpur police station. The two went missing around 4pm on Wednesday from their Cornfield Row residence. Rizwan lodged a missing diary around 11pm and the two were traced early this morning, roaming aimlessly.

 Talat Parveen, who had contracted an infection after a broken piece of needle was stitched up inside her body during delivery at Lady Dufferin Victoria Hospital, is recovering at Kothari Medical Centre, said doctors. She would have to stay at the hospital for a few more days.

 Dipak Bhattacharya, the chairman of North Dum Dum Municipality, was directed to pay a fine of Rs 2,000 for violating a court order by Justice K.J. Sengupta of Calcutta High Court on Thursday. The chairman had not obeyed an order directing him to issue a mutation certificate to Debayan Dutta Chowdhury, a resident of Dum Dum.

 The West Bengal Council of Higher Secondary (HS) Education on Thursday set up a digitised archive for preserving results and certificates of students. The marks and certificates of the students who have passed HS since 1978 are stored in the archive, inaugurated by school education minister Partha De. 




